A crack team of detectives from the Bayelsa State Police Command has arrested four suspected members of an armed robbery gang, who also belong to a cult group. This was contained in a statement on Wednesday by the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), SP Asinim Butswat. According to him, the suspects were nabbed on Tuesday at their hideout in the Amarata area of Yenagoa, the state capital. Butswat said two pistols, ammunition and a Barret with cult insignia were recovered from the suspects. He said, “The operatives carried out a sting operation at the hideout of the gang at Amarata community, Yenagoa, on 22nd March, 2022, at about 0630 hours. “Preliminary investigation reveals that the suspects, one Seibokuro Keme Bradikumo ‘m’ 32 years; Agoli Frank ‘m’ 30 years; Ebi Newton ‘m’ 29 years; and Dume Odigom Bright ‘m’ 24 years, were responsible for recent robberies in Amarata and environs. “During a search on their hideout, police operatives recovered a Makarov pistol, .9mm ammunition, a locally made pistol, Cartridges, and a black barret with the inscription “Deebam 1991”. POLL “The suspects have confessed to membership of Bobos cult group and are cooperating with the police in its investigation.”